      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:21:8",
      "text": [
        " كُلُّ دَاءٍ مِنَ التُّخَمَةِ مَا خَلَا الْحُمَّى فَإِنَّهَا تَرِدُ وُرُوداً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "From him, from Muhammad Bin Ali, from Ibn Sinan, from the one who mentioned it, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Every illness is from the satiation apart from the fever, for it arrives gradually’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "8. It is narrated from the narrator of the previous Hadith from Muhammad ibn Ali from ibn Sinan from those whom he has mentioned who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ’Every illness is because of overeating except, fever (infection) which enters the body.’” "
        ]
      }
